Sentencas: Lanthanum doped strontium titanate gadolinium doped cerium oxide (LST-GDC) anodic layers are sintered in air and further reduced in-situ at low temperature (750 degrees C) avoiding usually performed pre-reduction treatment at high temperature.
Titulo: On the manufacturing of low temperature activated Sr0.9La0.1TiO3-δCe1-xGdxO2-δ anodes for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The influence of various milling techniques and of powders with different specific surface area, on the microstructures of screen-printed anodes, is investigated.
Titulo: On the manufacturing of low temperature activated Sr0.9La0.1TiO3-δCe1-xGdxO2-δ anodes for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The combination of milling and sonication processes is efficient in reducing aggregation of the anode powders.
Titulo: On the manufacturing of low temperature activated Sr0.9La0.1TiO3-δCe1-xGdxO2-δ anodes for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The anode performance is improved when a planetary milling step is involved in the preparation of the screen printing inks.
Titulo: On the manufacturing of low temperature activated Sr0.9La0.1TiO3-δCe1-xGdxO2-δ anodes for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The use of gadolinium doped cerium oxide with high specific surface area decreases the polarization resistance.
Titulo: On the manufacturing of low temperature activated Sr0.9La0.1TiO3-δCe1-xGdxO2-δ anodes for solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The rate of hydrogen oxidation is also enhanced by increasing porosity.
Titulo: On the manufacturing of low temperature activated Sr0.9La0.1TiO3-δCe1-xGdxO2-δ anodes for solid oxide fuel cell
